05/04/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew I held a paschal liturgy in Istanbul on Sunday (April 4th). 
The service was attended by many Christians living in Turkey, as well as numerous tourists. 
Earlier in the day, Turkey's State Minister and chief EU negotiator Egemen Bagis greeted all Christians and wished those living in Turkey a happy and peaceful holiday. 
(Zaman, Anadolu news agency - 04/04/10)
